      "author": "opa-oz",
      "description": "# Obsidian Snippets Plugin\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\n\r\nThe other day I though - \"Why am I still installing my CSS snippets manually? I can make it easier!\"\r\n\r\n## How to use it\r\n\r\n1. Install & enable Plugin;\r\n2. Go to `Settings` -> `Snippets Plugin`;\r\n3. Download any amount of snippets you like;\r\n4. Activate newly downloaded snippets at `Settings` -> `Appearance`.\r\n\r\n> [!Note]\r\n> Available snippets are being pulled from [opa-oz/obsidian-snippets](https://github.com/opa-oz/obsidian-snippets). Feel free to contribute, or switch to your own repository\r\n",
